How to choose the mattress and the dreamer: women and men are looking for different things
Nothing of a pumping frame for the bed; what really confers its quality on a good bed is the surface to bury, i.e. the mattress and the dreamer.
First and foremost, they must be perfectly complemented in order to be adapted to specific users.
During the selection, numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, health status and sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and the dreamer are located is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that doesn’t usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they “heat” more slowly.
In addition, they usually weigh considerably more than regular polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more often.
If the channels of the center are not properly aired and, above, are on a firm base, they keep inside the moisture.
When choosing a bed, they also influence habits.
Those who have spent a long time abroad often wear a very high mattress with a soft layer and will have trouble feeling good on a lower and harder surface.
“Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn’t sleep as well here.
"For their crooked shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
“This type of mattress is also recommended for people with diabetes who sometimes have problems with the nervous system, so they poorly receive information from the joints and skin,” explains Sylva Hadamczikova, who specializes in mattress furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italians Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to be able to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This “miracle” works in a very simple way.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to your body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not turn around like after a hard game.
He just sleeps better.
Viscoelastic also acts as a protection against wounds.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to your height the length of your feet, i.e. between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for a person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example singles, it is recommended at least between 120 and 140 cm.
So that a possible visit is also comfortable.
"If not, a simple rule can be applied to calculate the width: when tumbling mouth up, you should have your hands comfortably tightened towards the elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, an expert from Cechu <0xC4><0x8C>alouník<0xC5><0xAF> to decoratér<0xC5><0xAF>, who has been dealing with the mobile theme of the ergonone in the special health of the dream.
In the double rooms, each needs its own dreamer and mattress, so during the purchase you need to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the dreamers at different heights, which is not always possible on all beds.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, models with inner springs at least 15 cm, of which at least three cm are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softness.
“By touching it with your hand or by accommodating it on the mattress, the springs should certainly not be noticed,” Helena Prokopová warns.
Each mattress requires a certain type of dream.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
