For this reason, experts reject slogans that speak of a lifespan of the mattress up to 25 years or even a lifetime warranty.
However, everything has a but.
Therefore, sellers give a tip: in mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, carefully care for cleaning and washing the case, but better add a mattress protector that can be removed and washed easily.
Although zippered mattresses are currently manufactured in all their perimeter, so when they are opened they are left in two parts (something very important for washing and washing machine size!), their manipulation in larger models (and by one person) when lifting the mattress can look like a weight struggle and a weight struggle.
In bed, instead of a dreamer, do you have a firm table?
Never! Never!
As much for the beds designed for one night visits.
However, you should make (if you no longer have) ventilation holes in the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For sommers of non-articulable sheets and containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although it is always better to sommer with a larger number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lumbar area can be re-forged and re-forged.
Articulated sheet sommers should not be used with a spring mattress, as it does not react to reclining.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
