At the moment, the device is about the size of a flashlight box, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people feared the case of the missing Ani<0xC4><0x8D>ka and began to report on the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
“We’re all trying to say that it’s not a spy, but another way to reduce the likelihood of a tragedy,” says Petr Pilin of the company Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example, if they are put in someone’s pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases.”
