For example, in Peru, where economic growth has reached an average of 6 per cent annually since 2002, support for democracy has increased from a decrease of 40 per cent in 2005 to 61 per cent this year.
It also grew in Mexico, where the economy has recovered after suffering a major decline in production last year.
