“First, the external qualities of candidates will determine whether they meet the requirements, such as height, weight, facial features, etc.”
Then comes the temperament "and the inner qualities".
Female chengguans are like florists, he said, adding, "in addition to being florists, they will have other responsibilities."
Zheng Lihua, deputy director of the district city administration office, is not anxious to back that description.
But he noted that height requirements were standard in many Chinese job notices for both sexes.
Then comes the demand for harmonious facial features.
