Certainly, the disabled or disfigured should not be presented.
“We can’t allow a person to catch or a robber to come to work here,” Mr. Zheng said.
"His image would not be good."
Liu Yi, who patrols Baoguang Square near a monastery, is 22 years old, with his colored cheeks and a subtly curved mouth.
She doesn’t think the emphasis on her appearance is sexist, she said.
"Do you think I look sexy with this uniform?" he asked with a sardonic look.
His colleague with today’s people, 21-year-old Xu Yang, said “Our work must present the image of the city.”
They also don’t object to their fixed-time work, they said, because they house greater career ambitions than simply harassing sellers on the streets where they are supposed to circumscribe their business.
