Sport and Fraud Law
Traps like those of Alonso and Ramos in front of the Ajax show ingenuity but not willingness to escape a penalty.
The alleged expulsion by two Real Madrid players (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) in the game played on November 23 against Ajax in the Champions League has caused ink rivers to be written about whether such behavior is anti-sportive and whether, eventually, both players should be sanctioned by the UEF.
As is well known, after a few minutes to finish the game (which his team had already clearly won), the two players deliberately lost time to draw laps to cause the referee to show them the second yellow card.
