Secondly, the idea that any hacker can consult the most secret secrets of the world’s most powerful country significantly affects the State Department’s prestige.
Therefore, the scandal affects both the victims and the “verdugos”.
But we enter into the true nature of what has happened.
Formerly, in Orwell’s time, he could conceive at all power as a Big Brother who controlled every gesture of his subjects.
Orwell’s prophecy has come true since, being able to control every movement thanks to the phone, every transaction made, hotel visited, highway taken, the citizen thus became a complete victim of the eye of power.
